text.section:
Any local government may by ordinance establish one (1) or more neighborhood redevelopment zones. Such zones shall be substantially residential in character and shall consist chiefly of residential buildings at least twenty-five (25) years of age. To be eligible for designation as a neighborhood redevelopment zone the area shall be found by the legislative body to be characterized by:
Deteriorating housing stock;
Abandoned residential buildings or vacant lots where the dwelling has been demolished by fire, vandalism or as an unsafe structure;
Such other characteristics which cause the legislative body of the local government to believe the neighborhood is in a deteriorating economic and physical condition; or
Such detrimental conditions that the effect is to discourage mortgagees from making loans for, and present or prospective property owners from investing in the purchase and rehabilitation of residential buildings.
